根据官方报道，贝尔斯于当地时间凌晨3点戴着[[夜視鏡|夜视镜]]离开了贝兰拜营地。<ref name="nj">{{cite news|title=Afghans Want to Know if U.S. Soldier Acted Alone|first=John|last=Hudson|url=http://www.nationaljournal.com/nationalsecurity/afghans-want-to-know-if-u-s-soldier-acted-alone-20120312|journal=[[National_Journal|National Journal]]|date=12 March 2012|access-date=13 March 2012|archive-date=2015-05-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150511081950/http://www.nationaljournal.com/nationalsecurity/afghans-want-to-know-if-u-s-soldier-acted-alone-20120312|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Staff Sgt. Robert Bales' Neighbors Described Afghan Massacre Suspect As 'Good Guy'|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Blotter/sgt-robert-bales-family-man-good-soldier/story?id=15942005#.T2UEkFE5is8|access-date=2012-04-22|date=2012-03-17|publisher=Abcnews.go.com|archive-date=2021-04-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210419113917/https://abcnews.go.com/Blotter/sgt-robert-bales-family-man-good-soldier/story?id=15942005#.T2UEkFE5is8|dead-url=no}}</ref> 贝尔斯外出时不仅身穿[[陸軍作戰服|陆军作战服]]还额外穿着当地的传统服饰。<ref>{{cite news|title=Revealed: Rogue US soldier dressed in Afghan clothes and wore night goggles to embark on mission of murder|url=http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/uk-world-news/2012/03/13/revealed-rogue-us-soldier-dressed-in-afghan-clothes-and-wore-night-goggles-to-embark-on-mission-of-murder-86908-23786478/|newspaper=Daily Record|date=13 March 2012|access-date=14 March 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120329113242/http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/uk-world-news/2012/03/13/revealed-rogue-us-soldier-dressed-in-afghan-clothes-and-wore-night-goggles-to-embark-on-mission-of-murder-86908-23786478/|archive-date=29 March 2012}}</ref><ref>[http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/46714928/ns/local_news-clarksburg_wv/t/afghan-villagers-recount-weekend-shooting-rampage/ Afghan villagers recount weekend shooting rampage] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120319063918/http://www.msnbc.msn.com/id/46714928/ns/local_news-clarksburg_wv/t/afghan-villagers-recount-weekend-shooting-rampage|date=19 March 2012}}, ''[[MSNBC|MSNBC]]'' (13 March 2012)</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Killings baffle investigators|url=http://www.thenewstribune.com/2012/03/15/2067581/killings-baffle-investigators.html|newspaper=[[The_News_Tribune|The News Tribune]]|date=15 March 2012|access-date=15 March 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://archive.today/20120917145513/http://www.thenewstribune.com/2012/03/15/2067581/killings-baffle-investigators.html|archive-date=17 September 2012}}</ref><ref name="USAToday" />

据了解情况的政府官员说，屠杀是分两个阶段进行的，贝尔斯在这两个阶段之间还曾返回过营地。一名阿富汗警卫报告称，贝尔斯在凌晨1:30曾返回过营地，而另一名警卫报告称，贝尔斯在凌晨2:30分离开了营地。<ref name="ap-2phase">{{cite web|url=http://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/U/US_US_AFGHANISTAN_BALES?SITE=AP&SECTION=HOME&TEMPLATE=DEFAULT&CTIME=2012-03-24-16-50-23|access-date=26 March 2012|title=存档副本|archive-date=2021-05-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210517043434/https://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/U/US_US_AFGHANISTAN_BALES?SITE=AP&SECTION=HOME&TEMPLATE=DEFAULT&CTIME=2012-03-24-16-50-23|dead-url=yes}}{{cbignore|bot=medic}}</ref> 据信，贝尔斯首先是去了贝兰拜营地以北约0.8公里的阿尔科扎伊村，随后则去向营地以南2.4公里的巴兰迪村。<ref>Murphy, Kim and Ned Parker, "Afghan Massacre A Hard Case For Army", ''[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]'', 5 November 2012, p. 1</ref> 而在屠杀事件中，阿尔科扎伊村有4人死亡，6人受伤，巴兰迪村则有12人死亡。营地的美国哨兵听到了阿尔科扎伊村方向的枪声并向村庄方向观望，但哨兵并没有采取任何实质性的行动。<ref>Murhpy, Kim, "U.S. Soldiers Heard Gunfire But Didn't Act", ''[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]'', 7 November 2012, p.21</ref> 截至3月22日，美国当局确认有16人死亡，包括9名儿童、4名男子和3名妇女。<ref name="USAToday" /> 3月22日，死亡数字则被修正为17人，<ref name="usatoday2">{{cite news|title=U.S. now counts 17 dead in Afghan massacre|url=https://www.usatoday.com/news/world/afghanistan/story/2012-03-22/17-dead-in-afghan-massacre/53704660/1|agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]]|newspaper=[[USA_Today|USA Today]]|date=22 March 2012|access-date=22 March 2012|archive-date=2012-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120323010545/http://www.usatoday.com/news/world/afghanistan/story/2012-03-22/17-dead-in-afghan-massacre/53704660/1|dead-url=no}}</ref> 但随后又改为16人。<ref name="dropped">{{cite news|title=Army drops one charge against soldier accused in Afghan massacre|work=Reuters|date=1 June 2012|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2012/06/01/us-usa-crime-afghanistan-idUSBRE8501D520120601|access-date=26 June 2012|archive-date=2012-06-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120606162320/http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/06/01/us-usa-crime-afghanistan-idUSBRE8501D520120601|dead-url=yes}}</ref>据初步报道，另有5人受伤，而最终受伤人数则是6人。<ref name="USAToday" />

其中有一个家庭的四名成员在阿尔科扎伊村被杀。<ref name="Globe" /> 据一名腿部中弹的16岁男孩称，贝尔斯在开枪之前还叫醒了在睡梦中的家人。<ref name="yahooafp" /> 另一名目击者称，她看到这名男子把一名女子拖出家门，并多次将她的头往墙上撞。<ref>{{cite news|title=Afghan massacre: US soldier 'acted alone' in Kandahar|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-17343437|work=[[BBC|BBC]]|date=12 March 2012|access-date=18 March 2012|archive-date=2021-08-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210822221406/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-17343437|dead-url=no}}</ref>

而在巴兰迪村的第一个受害者则是Mohamed Dawood。据Dawood的哥哥称，贝尔斯直接朝Dawood的头部开了一枪，但在Dawood的妻子朝贝尔斯疯狂喊叫后，贝尔斯放过了她的妻子和六个孩子。<ref>Levinson, Charles, "Afghan Father Copes With Aftermath", ''[[Wall_Street_Journal|Wall Street Journal]]'', 23 March 2012, p. 7.</ref>

Abdul Samad的11名家人在巴兰迪村的家里被贝尔斯屠杀殆尽，这其中包括他的妻子、4个2-6岁的女孩、4个8-12岁的男孩和另外两个亲戚。<ref name="home">{{cite news|title=An Afghan Comes Home to a Massacre|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/13/world/asia/us-army-sergeant-suspected-in-afghanistan-shooting.html?_r=1|newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|date=12 March 2012|access-date=13 March 2012|first1=Taimoor|last1=Shah|first2=Graham|last2=Bowley|archive-date=2019-04-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190427155752/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/13/world/asia/us-army-sergeant-suspected-in-afghanistan-shooting.html?_r=1|dead-url=no}}</ref> 据一名目击者称“他拽住男孩们的头发，并拿枪朝他们的嘴里开枪”，<ref>{{cite news|title=US Soldier Accused in Afghanistan Massacre|url=http://weareaustin.com/news/top-stories/stories/vid_799.shtml|work=[[KEYE-TV|KEYE-TV]]|date=12 March 2012|access-date=13 March 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120504005239/http://weareaustin.com/news/top-stories/stories/vid_799.shtml|archive-date=4 May 2012}}</ref> 这造成至少有三名儿童被射中头部死亡，<ref name="BBC" /> 随后他们的尸体随被纵火焚烧。而另一名55岁的平民Mohammad Dawoud则在村里的另一所房子里被杀。<ref>{{cite news|title=Afghan-massacre suspect Staff Sgt. Robert Bales en route to U.S.|url=http://www.mcclatchydc.com/2012/03/16/142253/afghan-massacre-suspect-staff.html|publisher=[[The_McClatchy_Company|The McClatchy Company]]|date=16 March 2012|access-date=18 March 2012|archive-date=2014-05-21|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140521032151/http://www.mcclatchydc.com/2012/03/16/142253/afghan-massacre-suspect-staff.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 目击者称，贝尔斯的武器上装备有探照灯。<ref>Johnson, Kirk, "At Soldier's Hearing, Grisly Descriptions of Chaos And Horror", ''[[New_York_Times|New York Times]]'', 11 November 2012, p. 1</ref><ref>Murphy, Kim, "Young Afghan Victims Testify About Massacre", ''[[Los_Angeles_Times|Los Angeles Times]]'', 12 November 2012, p. 10</ref>

由于贝尔斯在屠杀中对受害者的尸体进行了焚尸，这在[[伊斯蘭教法|伊斯兰教法]]里被认为是一种亵渎行为。.<ref>{{cite news|title=Taliban vows revenge for apparent attack by U.S. soldier that killed 16 Afghan civilians|url=http://www.theblaze.com/stories/taliban-vows-revenge-for-apparent-attack-by-u-s-soldier-that-killed-16-afghan-civilians/|work=[[The_Blaze_(web_site)|The Blaze]]|date=12 March 2012|access-date=15 March 2012|archive-date=2012-09-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120904041125/http://www.theblaze.com/stories/taliban-vows-revenge-for-apparent-attack-by-u-s-soldier-that-killed-16-afghan-civilians/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 一位目击者称，一户11口之家的所有成员皆是头部中弹，随后尸体还被锐器扎刺，然后行凶者将所有尸体聚集在一间屋子里并点燃火焚尸。<ref name="home" /><ref>{{cite news|title=Afghans Bury Victims of American Soldier's Rampage as Restraint Is Urged|url=http://www.businessweek.com/news/2012-03-12/afghans-bury-victims-of-american-soldier-s-rampage-as-restraint-is-urged|magazine=[[Bloomberg_Businessweek|Bloomberg Businessweek]]|date=12 March 2012|access-date=13 March 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120315073251/http://www.businessweek.com/news/2012-03-12/afghans-bury-victims-of-american-soldier-s-rampage-as-restraint-is-urged|archive-date=15 March 2012}}</ref> 在一名受害者家里的地板上发现了一大堆灰烬，还发现一具部分被烧焦的儿童尸体。<ref>{{cite news|title=How it happened: Massacre in Kandahar|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-17334643|work=[[BBC|BBC]]|date=13 March 2012|access-date=13 March 2012|archive-date=2021-10-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211011054639/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-17334643|dead-url=no}}</ref> [[纽约时报|《纽约时报》]]的一名记者检查了被送往附近美国军事基地的儿童尸体，记者报告称一些儿童的腿部和头部均有烧伤。

==== 自首和认罪 ====
在对阿尔科扎伊村和巴兰迪村的屠杀后，贝尔斯向[[駐阿富汗國際維和部隊|驻阿富汗国际维和部队]]自首。<ref name="BBC">{{cite news|title=U.S. soldier kills Afghan civilians in Kandahar|publisher=BBC|date=11 March 2012|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-17332398|access-date=11 March 2012|archive-date=2021-08-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210819104907/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-17332398|dead-url=no}}</ref> 阿富汗军队发现他在屠杀发生之前就已经从前哨营地离开，美军营地的指挥官在发现有士兵失踪后理解集合部队并进行了人数统计。营地方面派出了一支巡逻队寻找失踪的士兵，但是在他屠杀后返回基地之前，这支巡逻队并没有找到他。据营地报告，贝尔斯在被拘留时也没有任何异常表现，而在发生枪击事件时，该地区也没有任何军事行动。<ref name="CNN">{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2012/03/11/world/asia/afghanistan-us-service-member/index.html?hpt=hp_t2|title=U.S. soldier accused of Afghan killing spree|publisher=CNN|date=11 March 2012|access-date=12 March 2012|archive-date=2021-05-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210506230830/https://www.cnn.com/2012/03/11/world/asia/afghanistan-us-service-member/index.html?hpt=hp_t2|dead-url=no}}</ref>

据报道，从该美军营地提供的监控录像显示：”贝尔斯披着传统的阿富汗围巾向营地走来，随后，他脱下围巾并把武器放在地上，然后举起双手投降。”<ref name="video">{{cite news|title=Defense Secretary Panetta arrives in Afghanistan on unannounced visit after shooting rampage|url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2012/03/14/defense-secretary-panetta-arrives-in-afghanistan-on-unannounced-visit-after/|work=[[Fox_News_Channel|Fox News]]|agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]]|date=14 March 2012|access-date=15 March 2012|archive-date=2014-08-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140820130316/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2012/03/14/defense-secretary-panetta-arrives-in-afghanistan-on-unannounced-visit-after/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 但该视频尚未向公众公开。

美方调查人员怀疑贝尔斯可能在午夜前就离开了基地，随后在阿尔科扎伊村犯下谋杀，然后在凌晨1点30分左右返回基地，在凌晨2时30分又离开了基地，并在巴兰迪村犯下谋杀，但在第二次出发后就引起了营地的警戒，导致营地出动巡逻队寻找失踪的贝尔斯。<ref>Burns, Robert, "Officials: Villagers Killed in Two Separate Attacks", ''[[Washington_Post|Washington Post]]'', 25 March 2012, p. 13.</ref>

据美国国防官员称，贝尔斯一回到营地就说:“是我干的”，然后还告诉营地的人们他做了什么。<ref name="ididit">{{cite news|title=Afghan Massacre Suspect: 'I Did It'|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Blotter/afghan-delegation-fire-site-massacre/story?id=15908068#.T2E3o8UltIM|work=[[ABC_News|ABC News]]|date=13 March 2012|access-date=14 March 2012|archive-date=2012-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314004407/https://abcnews.go.com/Blotter/afghan-delegation-fire-site-massacre/story?id=15908068#.T2E3o8UltIM|dead-url=no}}</ref> 后来，他聘请了一名律师，并拒绝与调查人员做进一步交谈。<ref name="ididit" /> 2012年3月14日，美国将贝尔斯从阿富汗空中押运到科威特，<ref name="cnnflown">{{cite news|title=Suspect in Afghan killings flown to Kuwait|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2012/03/14/world/asia/afghanistan-shooting/index.html|work=[[CNN|CNN]]|date=14 March 2012|access-date=15 March 2012|archive-date=2021-06-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210627191127/https://edition.cnn.com/2012/03/14/world/asia/afghanistan-shooting/index.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 随后于3月16日移送到堪萨斯州{{Internal link helper/en|莱文沃斯堡|Fort Leavenworth}}的{{Internal link helper/en|纪律兵营|United States Disciplinary Barracks From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia}}。<ref name="yahoo1">Goodwin, Liz, "[https://news.yahoo.com/blogs/lookout/military-sources-name-army-sergeant-suspected-afghanistan-massacre-224453357.html Army Staff Sgt. Robert Bales named as suspect in Afghanistan massacre] {{Wayback|url=https://news.yahoo.com/blogs/lookout/military-sources-name-army-sergeant-suspected-afghanistan-massacre-224453357.html |date=20210627185814 }}", ''[[Yahoo!_News|Yahoo! News]]'', 17 March 2012.</ref> 一名五角大楼发言人表示，此举是出于“根据法律考虑”。<ref>{{cite news|title=U.S. Soldier Accused of Afghan Massacre Flown Out of Country|url=http://www.rferl.org/content/us_massacre_suspect_flown_out_of_afghanistan/24515946.html|work=[[Radio_Free_Europe/Radio_Liberty|Radio Free Europe/Radio Liberty]]|date=14 March 2012|access-date=14 March 2012|archive-date=2016-02-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203075113/http://www.rferl.org/content/us_massacre_suspect_flown_out_of_afghanistan/24515946.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==== 行凶者人数 ====
据美国当局称，此次屠杀是完全由上士罗伯特·贝尔斯一人犯下。<ref>{{Cite news|title=U.S. Sergeant Is Said to Kill 16 Civilians in Afghanistan|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/12/world/asia/afghanistan-civilians-killed-american-soldier-held.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2012-03-11|accessdate=2021-06-16|issn=0362-4331|language=en-US|first=Taimoor|last=Shah|first2=Graham|last2=Bowley|archive-date=2019-05-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190527091651/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/12/world/asia/afghanistan-civilians-killed-american-soldier-held.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>美国军方向阿富汗当局展示了该营地的监控录像片段，以证明行凶者只有一人。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Defense Secretary Panetta arrives in Afghanistan on unannounced visit after shooting rampage|url=https://www.foxnews.com/politics/defense-secretary-panetta-arrives-in-afghanistan-on-unannounced-visit-after-shooting-rampage|access-date=2021-06-16|date=2015-03-25|work=Fox News|language=en-US|archive-date=2021-06-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210628211246/https://www.foxnews.com/politics/defense-secretary-panetta-arrives-in-afghanistan-on-unannounced-visit-after-shooting-rampage|dead-url=no}}</ref>

据[[路透社|路透社]]报道，遇难者的一些邻居和亲属看到一群美国士兵在凌晨2点左右到达他们的村庄，并进入房屋扫射。<ref name="Reuters">{{cite news|title=Western forces kill 16 civilians in Afghanistan: Kabul government|work=Reuters|date=11 March 2012|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/2012/03/11/us-afghanistan-civilians-idUSBRE82A02V20120311|access-date=11 March 2012|archive-date=2012-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120311070722/http://www.reuters.com/article/2012/03/11/us-afghanistan-civilians-idUSBRE82A02V20120311|dead-url=yes}}</ref>“他们就像全喝醉了一样，到处杀人，”邻居Agha Lala说道。<ref name="Reuters" /> 据《纽约时报》报道，一名幸存者和五名村民皆描述看到了一群士兵，而其他一些阿富汗村民称只看到了一名枪手。<ref name="NYT" /> 一些当地官员表示此次屠杀是有组织有计划的，他们声称如果没有帮助，一名士兵完全不可能实施这样的行动。<ref name="NYT" /><ref name="nj" /><ref>{{cite news|title=Afghans Skeptical Over Shooting Account|url=http://www.time.com/time/printout/0,8816,2108798,00.html|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130204131308/http://www.time.com/time/printout/0,8816,2108798,00.html|archive-date=4 February 2013|journal=[[Time_(magazine)|Time]]|agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]]|date=12 March 2012|access-date=13 March 2012|url-status=dead}}</ref>

2012年3月15日，由[[国民议会_(阿富汗)|阿富汗国民议会]]几名成员组成的阿富汗议会调查小组宣称，多达20名美国士兵参与了这起屠杀，<ref name="PAN">{{cite news|title=Up to 20 US troops executed Panjwai massacre: probe|url=http://www.pajhwok.com/en/2012/03/15/20-us-troops-executed-panjwai-massacre-probe|agency=[[Pajhwok_Afghan_News|Pajhwok Afghan News]]|date=15 March 2012|access-date=15 March 2012|archive-date=2020-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112034325/https://www.pajhwok.com/en/2012/03/15/20-us-troops-executed-panjwai-massacre-probe|dead-url=no}}</ref>在屠杀中还有两架[[直升機|直升机]]支援。 <ref>[[Bill_Roggio|Roggio, Bill]], "[http://www.longwarjournal.org/threat-matrix/archives/2012/03/afghan_parliament_delegation_c.php Afghan parliament delegation claims 15 US troops were involved in Kandahar massacre] {{Wayback|url=http://www.longwarjournal.org/threat-matrix/archives/2012/03/afghan_parliament_delegation_c.php |date=20140815075901 }}", ''[[Long_War_Journal|Long War Journal]]'', 17 March 2012.</ref> 调查小组在现场呆了两天，采访幸存者并收集证据。调查小组成员之一的Hamizai Lali说:“我们仔细检查了事故现场，并与失去亲人的家庭、受伤的人们和部落长老交谈……这些村庄距离美军基地1.5公里之远。我们相信一个士兵不可能在一个小时内在两个村庄杀死这么多人。”<ref name="PAN" />Hamizai Lali要求阿富汗政府、联合国和国际社会确保凶手在阿富汗受到惩罚。阿富汗总统[[哈米德·卡尔扎伊|哈米德·卡尔扎伊]]在访问受到屠杀影响的村庄中时指着其中一个村民说:“在他的家里，4个房间里的人都被杀光了，这个家庭里的儿童和妇女皆被杀害，然后他们的尸体被堆积在一个房间里焚尸，这样规模的杀戮是一个人办不到的。”<ref>{{cite news|title=Afghan leader blasts US over probe into shootings|url=https://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2012/03/16/nato-soldier-dies-in-attack-in-east-afghanistan|agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]]|magazine=[[U.S._News_&_World_Report|U.S. News & World Report]]|date=16 March 2012|access-date=17 March 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160203075113/http://www.usnews.com/news/world/articles/2012/03/16/nato-soldier-dies-in-attack-in-east-afghanistan|archive-date=3 February 2016}}</ref> 然而，该调查小组后来表示，他们也无法确认是否有多名士兵参与了屠杀。<ref>{{cite web|title=Afghan Officials Change Story: Kandahar Massacre May Have Only Had One Shooter|url=http://news.antiwar.com/2012/03/21/afghan-officials-change-story-kandahar-massacre-may-have-only-had-one-shooter/|access-date=2012-04-22|date=2012-03-21|publisher=News.antiwar.com|archive-date=2021-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629232139/https://news.antiwar.com/2012/03/21/afghan-officials-change-story-kandahar-massacre-may-have-only-had-one-shooter/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==== 对受害者家属的赔偿 ====
2012年3月25日，美国在[[坎大哈省|坎大哈省]]省长办公室向受害者家属发放了相当于86万美元的资金，每个遇难者将会获得5万美元，而每个伤者将会获得1万美元，但向受害者家属支付这笔资金的官员说，这笔钱并不是赔偿金，而是美国政府提供给受害者及其家人的人道援助。<ref>{{cite news|title=In Afghan killings, victim No. 17 remains unknown|url=http://www.cnn.com/2012/03/25/world/asia/afghanistan-killings-money/?hpt=hp_t1|work=CNN Wire Staff|publisher=CNN|access-date=26 March 2012|date=26 March 2012|archive-date=2016-03-04|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304064246/http://www.cnn.com/2012/03/25/world/asia/afghanistan-killings-money/?hpt=hp_t1|dead-url=no}}</ref>坎大哈省议会的一名成员称，这些款项是一种人道援助，但不是那种所谓要求“遇难者赦免罪行”的法律赔偿。<ref>{{cite news|last=Matthew|first=Rosenberg|title=U.S. Pays Families of Afghan Victims in Massacre by Soldier|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/26/world/asia/us-compensates-afghan-villagers-for-soldiers-attack.html?_r=1|work=The New York Times|access-date=26 March 2012|date=25 March 2012|archive-date=2021-06-30|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210630084416/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/26/world/asia/us-compensates-afghan-villagers-for-soldiers-attack.html?_r=1|dead-url=no}}</ref>

== 罗伯特·贝尔斯 ==
[[File:Robert_Bales.jpg|300x300px]]
{{Main|罗伯特·贝尔斯}}[[美国陆军|美国陆军]]认为，驻扎在贝兰拜军营的38岁陆军[[上士|上士]]罗伯特·贝尔斯是唯一应对枪击事件负责的人。<ref name="defense2">{{cite news|title=Army Identifies Afghanistan Shooting Suspect|url=http://www.defense.gov/news/newsarticle.aspx?id=67591|publisher=[[United_States_Department_of_Defense|United States Department of Defense]]|date=17 March 2012|access-date=18 March 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120414034640/http://www.defense.gov//News/NewsArticle.aspx?ID=67591|archive-date=14 April 2012}}</ref> 据[[美国国防部长|国防部长]][[莱昂·帕内塔|莱昂·帕内塔]]称，贝尔斯在被捕后立即承认了屠杀行为，并“告诉了别人到底发生了什么”。<ref>{{Cite web|title=Afghan Massacre Suspect: 'I Did It'|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Blotter/afghan-delegation-fire-site-massacre/story?id=15908068|access-date=2021-06-16|last=News|first=A. B. C.|work=ABC News|language=en|archive-date=2012-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314004407/https://abcnews.go.com/Blotter/afghan-delegation-fire-site-massacre/story?id=15908068|dead-url=no}}</ref>随后他聘请了一位律师，并拒绝与调查人员谈论他的动机和行为。<ref>{{cite news|title=Afghan Delegation Comes Under Fire at Site of Massacre|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/afghan-delegation-fire-site-massacre/story?id=15908068#.T1-OecUltIM|work=[[ABC_News|ABC News]]|date=13 March 2012|access-date=13 March 2012|archive-date=2012-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314031904/https://abcnews.go.com/International/afghan-delegation-fire-site-massacre/story?id=15908068#.T1-OecUltIM|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="lawyer2">{{cite news|title='Barefoot Bandit' lawyer to defend soldier in Afghan murders|url=http://content.usatoday.com/communities/ondeadline/post/2012/03/barefoot-bandit-lawyer-to-defend-solider-in-afghan-murders/1#|newspaper=[[USA_Today|USA Today]]|date=15 March 2012|access-date=16 March 2012|archive-date=2012-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318032557/http://content.usatoday.com/communities/ondeadline/post/2012/03/barefoot-bandit-lawyer-to-defend-solider-in-afghan-murders/1|dead-url=no}}</ref>

据官员称，贝尔斯其自身可能有婚姻问题，<ref name="ididit" /> 在枪击事件的调查中，美方调查了一封可能是激怒贝尔斯的关于婚姻问题的电子邮件。<ref name="lawyer" /> 他的妻子在她的博客上描述了对贝尔斯因为没有被晋升为上士（E-7）而感到失望<ref name="blog">{{cite news|title=Sergeant's Wife Kept a Blog on the Travails of Army Life|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/18/us/wife-of-accused-soldier-kept-blog-on-travails-of-army-life.html|newspaper=[[The_New_York_Times|The New York Times]]|date=17 March 2012|access-date=17 March 2012|first=Matt|last=Flegenheimer|archive-date=2012-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318033104/http://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/18/us/wife-of-accused-soldier-kept-blog-on-travails-of-army-life.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> ，贝尔斯的家庭同事也陷入了财务困境，枪击事件发生的前三天，贝尔斯的妻子把他们的房子挂牌出售，因为他们得抵押拖欠的贷款。<ref name="mortgage">{{cite news|title=Sgt Robert Bales: The story of the soldier accused of murdering 16 Afghan villagers|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/9150641/Sgt-Robert-Bales-The-story-of-the-soldier-accused-of-murdering-16-Afghan-villagers.html|newspaper=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|date=17 March 2012|access-date=19 March 2012|location=London|first=Philip|last=Sherwell|archive-date=2012-03-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120319013339/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/northamerica/usa/9150641/Sgt-Robert-Bales-The-story-of-the-soldier-accused-of-murdering-16-Afghan-villagers.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2012年3月23日，美国政府指控贝尔斯犯有17项谋杀罪、6项谋杀未遂罪和6项袭击罪。<ref>{{cite news|title=Robert Bales to be charged with 17 counts of murder|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2012/mar/22/robert-bales-17-counts-murder-afghanistan|agency=Associated Press|newspaper=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|date=22 March 2012|access-date=22 March 2012|location=London|archive-date=2021-06-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210627180541/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2012/mar/22/robert-bales-17-counts-murder-afghanistan|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2012年3月24日，美国调查人员称，他们认为贝尔斯将巴兰迪村和阿尔科扎伊村分开屠杀，在第一次屠杀后贝尔斯就返回了贝兰拜营地，在一小时后则又再次从营地中出来。<ref>{{cite web|title=US Believes Accused Soldier Split Killing Spree - AP|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/us-believes-accused-soldier-split-killing-spree-15994471|access-date=22 April 2012|work=ABC News|archive-date=2012-03-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120327023301/https://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/us-believes-accused-soldier-split-killing-spree-15994471|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在这次事件中，美国其他军事人员并没有因事件而受到纪律处分。

2013年8月22日，贝尔斯在军事法庭认罪，他为自己的屠杀行为忏悔，并将大屠杀描述为“其自己懦弱的行为”，贝尔斯的认罪最后使他免于死刑。<ref>{{cite news|title=Army sergeant says Afghan killing spree was 'act of cowardice'|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2013/08/22/us/robert-bales-afghan-killings/|work=CNN Staff|publisher=CNN|access-date=24 August 2013|date=22 August 2013|archive-date=2021-06-29|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210629014851/https://edition.cnn.com/2013/08/22/us/robert-bales-afghan-killings/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=U.S. soldier apologizes for Afghan shooting rampage|url=http://www.rawstory.com/rs/2013/08/23/u-s-soldier-apologizes-for-afghan-shooting-rampage/|access-date=24 August 2013|date=22 August 2013|last=Fergueson|first=David|website=The Raw Story|archive-date=2013-10-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131028181528/http://www.rawstory.com/rs/2013/08/23/u-s-soldier-apologizes-for-afghan-shooting-rampage/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 2013年8月23日，贝尔斯被法院判处终身监禁且不得假释。<ref name="Healy" /><ref>{{cite news|title=Staff Sgt. Robert Bales sentenced to life in prison without chance of parole for Afghanistan massacre that left 16 dead|url=http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/army-staff-sgt-robert-bales-life-chance-parole-article-1.1435117|access-date=24 August 2013|newspaper=NY Daily News via The Associated Press|date=23 August 2013|location=New York|archive-date=2013-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130826025142/http://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/army-staff-sgt-robert-bales-life-chance-parole-article-1.1435117|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Ashton|first=Adam|title=Staff Sgt. Bales Sentenced to Life in Prison for Murdering 16 Afghan Cilvilians|url=https://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/military/july-dec13/bales_08-23.html|access-date=24 August 2013|newspaper=The News Tribune via PBS Newshour|date=23 August 2013|archive-date=2013-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130824013443/http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/military/july-dec13/bales_08-23.html|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sgt. Bales sentenced to life in prison without parole for Afghan massacre|url=http://www.rawstory.com/rs/2013/08/23/sgt-bales-sentenced-to-life-in-prison-without-parole-for-afghan-massacre/|access-date=24 August 2013|date=23 August 2013|last=Kaufmann|first=Scott|website=The Raw Story|archive-date=2013-10-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20131027023102/http://www.rawstory.com/rs/2013/08/23/sgt-bales-sentenced-to-life-in-prison-without-parole-for-afghan-massacre/|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Weise|first=Elizabeth|title=Soldier gets life in prison for Afghan massacre|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2013/08/23/afghanistan-massacre-bales/2692917/|access-date=24 August 2013|newspaper=USA Today|date=23 August 2013|archive-date=2021-06-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210627223228/https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation/2013/08/23/afghanistan-massacre-bales/2692917/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 他被降职为军队最低军衔列兵(E-1)，并被开除军籍，军队也收到命令没收他所有的工资和津贴。<ref name="seattletimes">{{cite news|url=http://seattletimes.com/html/localnews/2019610961_apusafghanistanmassacre4thldwritethru.html|title=Prosecutor: US soldier had blood of victims on him|newspaper=[[The_Seattle_Times|The Seattle Times]]|date=5 November 2012|access-date=29 April 2013|author=Johnson, Gene|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130918180210/http://seattletimes.com/html/localnews/2019610961_apusafghanistanmassacre4thldwritethru.html|archive-date=18 September 2013}}</ref> 监督军事法庭的指挥官称可以选择将刑期减为无期徒刑并有可能得到假释。<ref name="APUSAToday20130823">{{cite news|title=Afghan villagers angered by Bales life sentence|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2013/08/23/villagers-unsatisfied-bales-sentence/2694043/|access-date=24 August 2013|agency=Associated Press|work=USA Today|date=23 August 2013|archive-date=2013-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130824013202/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/world/2013/08/23/villagers-unsatisfied-bales-sentence/2694043/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 阿富汗村民和受害者家属对美方这一判决感到极度不满，称他罪该万死。<ref name="APUSAToday20130823" /><ref name="PostGaz">{{cite news|title=Afghan villagers unsatisfied by life sentence for Bales|date=23 August 2013|agency=AP|work=Pittsburgh Post Gazette|url=http://www.post-gazette.com/stories/news/us/afghan-villagers-unsatisfied-by-life-sentence-for-bales-700581/|access-date=24 August 2013|first=Gene|last=Johnson|archive-date=2013-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130824054338/http://www.post-gazette.com/stories/news/us/afghan-villagers-unsatisfied-by-life-sentence-for-bales-700581/|dead-url=no}}</ref>

