==== 遇难者家属和阿富汗社会 ====
一名在事件中失去四名家庭成员的妇女说：“我们不知道为什么这个外国士兵会来杀害我们无辜的家庭成员。他不是喝醉了就是单纯喜欢杀害平民。”<ref name="NBC17">{{cite news|title=Karzai calls Afghan civilian deaths 'assassination'|url=http://www2.nbc17.com/news/2012/mar/11/11/us-soldier-accused-killing-civilians-shooting-ramp-ar-2029542/|work=[[WNCN|WNCN]]|date=11 March 2012|access-date=13 March 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120316021728/http://www2.nbc17.com/news/2012/mar/11/11/us-soldier-accused-killing-civilians-shooting-ramp-ar-2029542/|archive-date=16 March 2012}}</ref> 60岁的农民Abdul Samad失去了11名家庭成员，其中8人是儿童，他说：“我们的政府让我们重回村子，然后再纵容美国人杀了我们。”<ref name="home" /> 一位怀里抱着一个死去的婴儿悲伤母亲说：“他们杀了一个孩子，这个孩子是塔利班吗?”相信我，我还没见过一个只有两岁的塔利班成员。”<ref>{{cite news|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/us-soldier-accused-killing-16-afghans-including-women/story?id=15897098|title=U.S. Soldier Accused of Killing 16 Afghans, Including Women and Children|date=11 March 2012|access-date=13 March 2012|work=[[ABC_News|ABC News]]|archive-date=2019-04-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190403231004/https://abcnews.go.com/International/us-soldier-accused-killing-16-afghans-including-women/story?id=15897098|dead-url=no}}</ref>

“我不想要任何补偿！我不要钱，也不要房子，我也不想去麦加朝圣，你知道我想要什么吗？我现在非常想要这些犯下罪行的美国人得到应有的报应，这是我唯一的要求！唯一的要求！唯一的要求！”一位兄弟被杀的村民愤怒地说到。<ref name="msnbcend">{{cite news|title=Karzai says he's at 'end of the rope' with US over Afghanistan massacre|url=http://worldnews.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2012/03/16/10722610-karzai-says-hes-at-end-of-the-rope-with-us-over-afghanistan-massacre|work=[[MSNBC|MSNBC]]|date=17 March 2012|access-date=17 March 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120319061242/http://worldnews.msnbc.msn.com/_news/2012/03/16/10722610-karzai-says-hes-at-end-of-the-rope-with-us-over-afghanistan-massacre|archive-date=19 March 2012}}</ref>

300多名潘杰瓦伊当地居民聚集在美军营地周围抗议屠杀行为。<ref name="NYT Panjwai">{{cite news|title=Army Sergeant Accused of Slaying 16 in Afghan Villages|author=Taimoor Shah|author2=Graham Bowley|work=The New York Times|date=11 March 2012|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/12/world/asia/afghanistan-civilians-killed-american-soldier-held.html|access-date=11 March 2012|archive-date=2019-05-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190527091651/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/12/world/asia/afghanistan-civilians-killed-american-soldier-held.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 一些人带来在村庄里被焚尸后而烧过的毯子以代表死者。<ref name="NYT" /> 在一间房子里，一位老妇人尖叫道:“愿上帝杀了卡尔扎伊的独子，让他体会体会我们现在此时此刻的感受。”<ref name="yahooafp">{{cite news|title=US vows to probe soldier's deadly Afghan rampage|url=https://news.yahoo.com/rogue-us-soldier-kills-wounds-16-afghans-100025247.html|agency=[[Agence_France-Presse|Agence France-Presse]]|date=11 March 2012|access-date=12 March 2012|archive-date=2012-03-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120314140832/http://news.yahoo.com/rogue-us-soldier-kills-wounds-16-afghans-100025247.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>3月13日，数百名大学生在阿富汗东部城市[[賈拉拉巴德_(阿富汗)|贾拉拉巴德]]抗议，<ref name="tel">{{cite news|title=Hundreds take to streets to protest at killing of 16 Afghan civilians|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/afghanistan/9139762/Hundreds-take-to-streets-to-protest-at-killing-of-16-Afghan-civilians.html|newspaper=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Daily Telegraph]]|date=13 March 2012|access-date=13 March 2012|location=London|archive-date=2018-10-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181013014301/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/afghanistan/9139762/Hundreds-take-to-streets-to-protest-at-killing-of-16-Afghan-civilians.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 学生高呼“美国去死，奥巴马去死”，并焚烧美国总统的肖像和[[十字架_(基督教)|基督教十字架]]。<ref name="tel" /><ref>{{cite news|title=Afghan Villagers Recount Weekend Shooting Rampage|url=https://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/students-protest-us-soldier-killed-afghans-15907521#.T2ApxxHxpIE|agency=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]]|work=[[ABC_News|ABC News]]|date=13 March 2012|access-date=13 March 2012|archive-date=2012-03-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120318062744/http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/students-protest-us-soldier-killed-afghans-15907521#.T2ApxxHxpIE|dead-url=no}}</ref> 3月15日，大约2000人参加了南部[[扎布尔省|扎布尔省]]的另一次抗议活动。<ref name="ourboy">{{cite news|title=Afghan massacre US soldier 'reluctant to serve'|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-17395066|work=BBC|date=16 March 2012|access-date=15 March 2012|archive-date=2012-03-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120316090659/http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-17395066|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==== 阿富汗当局 ====
[[阿富汗总统|阿富汗总统]][[哈米德·卡尔扎伊|哈米德·卡尔扎伊]]称这一事件为“蓄意谋杀”，并称“这是一次对无辜平民的有针对性屠杀，是不可原谅的。”<ref name="BBC" /><ref name="Globe">{{cite news|title=NATO apologizes after U.S. soldier opens fire on Afghan civilians|author=Heidi Vogt|author2=Mirwais Kha|work=The Globe and Mail|location=Canada|date=11 March 2012|url=https://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/africa-mideast/nato-apologizes-after-us-soldier-opens-fire-on-afghan-civilians/article2365781/|access-date=11 March 2012|archive-date=2012-03-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120315121143/http://www.theglobeandmail.com/news/world/africa-mideast/nato-apologizes-after-us-soldier-opens-fire-on-afghan-civilians/article2365781/|dead-url=no}}</ref> 他说，美国现在必须从阿富汗农村地区撤军，并让阿富汗国民军维持当地秩序并减少美军造成的平民伤亡。卡尔扎伊在3月16日表示，美国方面对此次屠杀事件的调查工作完全没有做到应有的配合。<ref name="bbcbales">{{cite news|title=Afghanistan massacre suspect named as Sgt Robert Bales|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-17411009|work=BBC|date=17 March 2012|access-date=17 March 2012|archive-date=2021-06-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210627231142/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-17411009|dead-url=no}}</ref> 他补充到：“北约部队造成的平民伤亡问题已经持续太久了……是该解决这个问题的时候了。”<ref name="msnbcend" />[[內務部_(阿富汗)|阿富汗内政部]]发言人以“最强烈的措辞”谴责了这一行为。<ref name="Globe" />

阿富汗当地的政客希望贝尔斯在阿富汗接受本地法庭的审判。<ref name="bostonglobe1">{{cite news|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/news/world/2012/03/12/afghans-voice-rage-over-civilian-deaths-defends-mission/5fe1tEOA7IjFnkXPY7AH4K/story.html|title=Calls for justice follow deaths of Afghan civilians|work=The Washington Post|date=13 March 2012|publisher=The Boston Globe|access-date=13 March 2012|author=Londoño, Ernesto|archive-date=2021-06-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210627215510/https://www.bostonglobe.com/news/world/2012/03/12/afghans-voice-rage-over-civilian-deaths-defends-mission/5fe1tEOA7IjFnkXPY7AH4K/story.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>阿富汗国民议会坚持要求在阿富汗公开审判美国士兵并称：“我们要求在阿富汗人民面前公开审判并严惩这个美国罪犯。”<ref name="parl">{{cite news|title=US soldier who killed villagers should be put on trial in Afghanistan, parliament demands|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/afghanistan/9137937/US-soldier-who-killed-villagers-should-be-put-on-trial-in-Afghanistan-parliament-demands.html|newspaper=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|date=12 March 2012|access-date=15 March 2012|location=London|archive-date=2021-06-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210628052909/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/afghanistan/9137937/US-soldier-who-killed-villagers-should-be-put-on-trial-in-Afghanistan-parliament-demands.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 国民议会还谴责屠杀是“极其残忍且不人道的”，并宣称“人们对外国军队的无知和滥暴行为正在失去耐心”。<ref name="parl3">{{cite news|title=US soldier who killed villagers should be put on trial in Afghanistan, parliament demands|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/afghanistan/9137937/US-soldier-who-killed-villagers-should-be-put-on-trial-in-Afghanistan-parliament-demands.html|newspaper=[[The_Daily_Telegraph|The Telegraph]]|date=12 March 2012|access-date=15 March 2012|location=London|archive-date=2021-06-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210628052909/https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/asia/afghanistan/9137937/US-soldier-who-killed-villagers-should-be-put-on-trial-in-Afghanistan-parliament-demands.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 一名来自坎大哈的国会议员Abdul Rahim Ayobi说：“枪击事件向我们传达了一个信息，那就是美国士兵已经失去了他们指挥官的控制。”<ref name="usat3">{{cite news|title=After Afghan massacre, how deep are the wounds?|url=https://www.usatoday.com/news/world/afghanistan/story/2012-03-12/panjwai-afghanistan-killings/53503494/1|newspaper=[[USA_Today|USA Today]]|date=12 March 2012|access-date=24 May 2021|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120323201905/https://www.usatoday.com/news/world/afghanistan/story/2012-03-12/panjwai-afghanistan-killings/53503494/1#|archive-date=23 March 2012}}</ref> 来自昆都士的一名议员Kamal Safai说：“尽管这是个人行为，但公众的反应情绪将会全部责怪美国到头上，而不是这个士兵。”<ref name="usat3" />

==== 美国及其北约 ====
美国和驻阿富汗国际维和部队皆对此屠杀事件道歉并承诺进行全面调查。国防部长莱昂·帕内塔表示，这名士兵“将被绳之以法并追究责任，我们会对他考虑死刑”。<ref name="bostonglobe1" /> [[美国总统|美国总统]][[贝拉克·奥巴马|奥巴马]]称这一事件是“令人心碎的悲剧”，但他指出，他对美军在阿富汗取得的成就“总体上感到满意和自豪”，<ref name="Fox">{{cite news|title=Obama calls Afghan shooting 'heartbreaking', says he's 'generally proud' of troops|newspaper=Fox News|agency=Associated Press|url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2012/03/12/obama-calls-afghan-shooting-heartbreaking-says-hes-generally-proud-troops/print|date=12 March 2012|access-date=13 March 2012|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120313022506/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2012/03/12/obama-calls-afghan-shooting-heartbreaking-says-hes-generally-proud-troops/print|archive-date=13 March 2012}}</ref> 并表示这一事件的发生并不代表美国军队的“素质”以及美国对阿富汗人民的尊重。<ref name="NYT">{{cite news|title=U.S. Sergeant Is Said to Kill 16 Civilians in Afghanistan|author=Taimoor Shah|author2=Graham Bowley|newspaper=The New York Times|date=11 March 2012|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/12/world/asia/afghanistan-civilians-killed-american-soldier-held.html|access-date=11 March 2012|archive-date=2019-05-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190527091651/https://www.nytimes.com/2012/03/12/world/asia/afghanistan-civilians-killed-american-soldier-held.html|dead-url=no}}</ref> 3月13日，奥巴马称：“美国将严肃对待此事，就像对待我们自己的公民和孩子被谋杀一样。我们对无辜生命的丧失感到痛心。杀害无辜平民是残暴且不可接受的。”<ref>{{cite web|title=Remarks by the President on Fair Trade|url=https://obamawhitehouse.archives.gov/the-press-office/2012/03/13/remarks-president-fair-trade|access-date=15 March 2012|date=13 March 2012|work=[[whitehouse.gov|whitehouse.gov]]|via=[[NARA|National Archives]]|archive-date=2021-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210311163244/https://obamawhitehouse.archives.gov/the-press-office/2012/03/13/remarks-president-fair-trade|dead-url=no}}</ref> 在回答记者是否可以把这次屠杀比作1968年[[美萊村屠殺|美莱村大屠杀]]里美国军队对南越平民残忍杀戮时，奥巴马回答说:“并没有可比性，这次屠杀完全由一个士兵实施的。”<ref name="MyLai-question">{{cite news|title=Obama: Afghan shooting rampage was work of lone gunman|first=Matt|last=Spetalnick|work=Reuters|url=http://in.reuters.com/article/2012/03/12/afghanistan-obama-urgent-idINDEE82B0IZ20120312|date=13 March 2012|access-date=13 March 2012|archive-date=2013-02-01|archive-url=https://archive.today/20130201062438/http://in.reuters.com/article/2012/03/12/afghanistan-obama-urgent-idINDEE82B0IZ20120312|dead-url=yes}}</ref>

驻阿富汗国际维和部队指挥官[[约翰·艾伦|约翰·艾伦]]将军也发表了道歉声明，同时北约驻阿富汗部队副指挥官阿德里安·布拉德肖也表示道歉:“我希望表达我深切的遗憾和失望……我无法解释这种无情行为背后的动机，但这绝不是驻阿富汗国际维和部队授权的军事行动。”<ref name="USAToday">{{cite news|title=U.S. servicemember opens fire on Afghans; at least 15 dead|agency=AP|work=USA Today|date=11 March 2012|url=https://www.usatoday.com/news/world/story/2012-03-11/afganistan-civilian-shootings/53472526/1|access-date=11 March 2012|archive-date=2012-03-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120311132750/http://www.usatoday.com/news/world/story/2012-03-11/afganistan-civilian-shootings/53472526/1|dead-url=no}}</ref> 政府承诺将进行“迅速彻底”的调查。<ref name="BBC" /> 美国官员表示，屠杀事件并不会影响他们在该地区的战略部署。<ref name="CNN" />

==== 塔利班 ====
[[塔利班|塔利班]]在其网站上发表声明称，“变态的美国野蛮人犯下了血腥和不人道的罪行。”<ref name="usat" /> 该激进组织向遇难者家属承诺，将为“每一位烈士”复仇。<ref name="usat" />塔利班还指责阿富汗安全官员参与了这次袭击。在发生致命暴行之后，塔利班取消了和平谈判。<ref name="ourboy" /> 3月13日，塔利班对访问屠杀现场的阿富汗政府代表团发动攻击，造成一名政府士兵死亡以及三名士兵被炸伤。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-17349736|title=Afghanistan militants 'attack Kandahar killings site'|work=[[BBC_Online|BBC Online]]|access-date=13 March 2012|date=13 March 2012|archive-date=2021-02-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210224001034/https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-17349736|dead-url=no}}</ref>

